&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you looking for a new and exciting challenge?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Do you have the ability to engage and motivate members within a team?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If so then this could be the role for you!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit an enthusiastic individual with a passion for learning and personal development to join our Catering Department as a Compliance &amp; Development Co-Ordinator.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The main purpose of the role is to undertake training, monitoring and ensure compliance with Food Safety and Health and Safety legislation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will require excellent organisational skills, be able to demonstrate the ability to work independently, using their own initiative and be willing to be adaptable and flexible to meet the needs of this very busy service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your duties will include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for fostering a consistent health &amp; safety aware culture within the Catering Department&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Carry out monthly health and safety audits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure health &amp; safety legislation is adhered to at all times&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Carry out investigations into Datix (AIRS) reports&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitoring of the food safety management system&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Carry out departmental food safety audits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay abreast of new legislation concerning food safety&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitoring compliance on statutory and mandatory training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Delivering of all departmental training and induction training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keeping departmental training matrix up to date&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate must be&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;IT Literate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A team player&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Customer focused&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to work to deadlines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to work under pressure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organised&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-motivated&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return we can offer you:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supportive &amp; friendly working environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Actively encouraged to learn and develop within your role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dedicated career pathways and great opportunities for continuing professional development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commitment to and support for your wellbeing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please Note: This vacancy may close prior to the closing date stated due to the high level of applications it may attract. If you would like to apply, please submit your application promptly to avoid disappointment.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: John Etterley&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Catering Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: john.etterley@ythfm.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;York Teaching Hospital Facilities Management LLP (YTHFM LLP) provides a full range of estates and facilities services to York Teaching Hospital NHS Foundation Trust, together with project management for capital investments. YTHFM LLP is a partnership between York Teaching Hospital NHS Foundation Trust and Northumbria Healthcare Facilities Management Limited. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;New starters will be employed by YTHFM and not directly by the NHS, however, they will enjoy the same terms and conditions as NHS staff covered by Agenda for Change. YTHFM employees have access to the NHS pension scheme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It&#39;s not just the area that&#39;s a great draw.In addition, as a member of our team you will receive a minimum of 27 days annual leave (on top of Bank Holidays) rising to 33 days after 10 years’ service and an award-winning package of staff benefits (see link on the right).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information about York Teaching Hospital Facilities Management type ythfm.co.uk in your internet search bar.&lt;/p&gt;
